This tutorial is based on the Lysozyme in Water example from Justin Lemkul in the VT Department of Biochemistry. See http://www.mdtutorials.com for a detailed explanation of each step of the example.

The new 2024 version supports PLUMED 2.9.2 integration which supports umbrella sampling, metadynamics, steered MD, path collective variable, etc.

See `gromacs_tinkercliffs_owl_cpu.sh` for a Slurm example script that can run on the CPU nodes of the TinkerCliffs and Owl clusters.

See `gromacs_falcon_gpu.sh` for a Slurm example script that can run on the GPU nodes of the Falcon cluster.